5. MIP Maturity Model
MIP maturity roadmap

Progression from discovery to enterprise intelligence.

Stage	Value
Inventory	1
Metadata	2
Graph	3
Reasoning	4
Copilot	5
Modernization	6

The mistake many organizations make is jumping directly to Level 5 (Copilot).

You should build:

Inventory
Metadata
Knowledge Graph
Reasoning
Copilot
Modernization

in that order.


What I would pitch to leadership

MIP is not a COBOL modernization tool.

It is:

An Enterprise Knowledge and Modernization Platform that continuously discovers, models, explains, and transforms legacy systems into understandable business capabilities.

That positioning makes it valuable not only for banking and card platforms but also for healthcare claims systems, telecom billing systems, insurance policy systems, government platforms, and any large legacy estate where business knowledge is trapped inside decades of code.